OL,3,C'Eating ice lollies should be part of
OL,4,Cprimary school curriculum'
OL,6,FThe Royal Society of Chemistry,
OL,7,FInstitute of Physics, Royal Society of
OL,8,FBiology and Association for Science
OL,9,FEducation have published
OL,10,Frecommendations for reforming the
OL,11,Fprimary school curriculum in a bid to
OL,12,Freduce inequalities in science,
OL,13,Ftechnology, engineering and
OL,14,Fmathematics (Stem) education.
OL,16,FEating ice lollies, playing musical
OL,17,Finstruments and planting vegetables
OL,18,Fare some of the listed experiences
OL,19,Fwhich they suggest children should
OL,20,Fhave by age 11 through science lessons
OL,21,Fin primary school.
